        public ImplicitCertificateData genImplicitCertificate(ImplicitCertificateData implicitCertData,
                                                      AlgorithmIndicator alg,

                                                      org.bouncycastle.jcajce.provider.asymmetric.ec.BCECPublicKey signerPublicKey,
                                                      org.bouncycastle.jcajce.provider.asymmetric.ec.BCECPrivateKey signerPrivateKey)
                                               throws java.io.IOException,
                                                      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException,
                                                      java.security.SignatureException
        Method that generates and sets the reconstruction value and related private key r value in the implicit certificate data structure.

        Important: The r value is not a part of the certificate.

        Parameters:
        implicitCertData - the certificate data structure with rv set as placeholder only, replaced with actual value in this metod.
        alg - related algorithm
        publicKey - the public key from the certificate request and used as basis for the reconstruction value.
        signerCert - the signing certificate (CA).
        signerPublicKey - the signing certificate public key.
        signerPrivateKey - the signing certificate private key.
        Returns:
        a newly generated implicit certificate data.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if communication problems occurred with underlying systems.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if argument was illegal
        java.security.SignatureException - if internal problems occurred generating the reconstruction value.
